Your Honor,

I stand before you today with a heavy heart, ready to accept responsibility for my actions and pleading guilty to the charge of assault. I want to express my deep remorse for my behavior and the harm that I have caused.

The incident occurred when my employee made a serious mistake at work, one that I knew would have severe financial consequences for my company. In a moment of extreme anger and frustration, I allowed my emotions to get the best of me. I pushed him to the ground and delivered a regrettable kick to his stomach. I fully acknowledge that my actions were unacceptable and inexcusable.

Immediately after the incident, I was overcome with regret and took immediate action to ensure the well-being of my employee. I did not hesitate to transport him to the nearest emergency room, fully aware of the seriousness of my actions and the potential harm that had been inflicted. It was a clear reflection of my immediate recognition of the gravity of the situation.

In light of this regrettable incident, I would like to take this opportunity to sincerely apologize to the victim and his family. I understand the physical and emotional pain that I have caused them, and I am truly sorry for the distress I have brought upon their lives. To demonstrate my remorse, I have already taken the initiative to offer to cover the remainder of his hospital bills. It is my hope that this gesture of reparation can provide some measure of relief to the victim and his family during this difficult time.

I must also emphasize that I am a 40-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. This regrettable incident is entirely out of character for me. I have always prided myself on being a responsible and law-abiding citizen, and I am truly devastated by my lapse in judgment.

Your Honor, I humbly ask for your consideration as I commend myself to the mercy of the court. I understand the gravity of my actions and the harm that I have caused, and I am committed to ensuring that such a reprehensible incident never occurs again. I have undergone self-reflection and counseling to address the anger management issues that contributed to this outburst, as well as the negative impact it has had on my personal and professional life.

I have suffered great emotional distress and personal anguish as a consequence of my actions. This ordeal has served as a harsh wake-up call, prompting me to recognize the need for significant personal growth and improvement. I am determined to learn from this experience and make the necessary changes to become a better person.

Additionally, I believe it is important to highlight my positive contributions to society. Throughout my life, I have strived to be a responsible and contributing member of my community. I have actively engaged in charitable activities and provided support to those in need. It is my sincere hope that these actions can serve as a testament to my inherent good character.

In closing, Your Honor, I stand here today with a plea of guilty, acknowledging the regrettable assault that took place. I understand the severity of my actions and the harm they caused, and I am fully prepared to accept the consequences. I respectfully ask for your leniency and consideration, taking into account my genuine remorse, my lack of a criminal record, and my commitment to personal growth and self-improvement.

Thank you for your attention and understanding.

Sincerely,
Aleksander Nowak

