1320
Your Honor,

I stand before you today with a deep sense of regret, prepared to accept responsibility for my actions and plead guilty to the charge of assault. I want to express my sincere remorse for the harm that I have caused.

The incident occurred when my employee made a serious mistake at work, one that I knew would have significant financial implications for my company. In a moment of anger and frustration, I pushed him to the ground and then kicked him in the stomach. It was a regrettable reaction, and I fully acknowledge that my behavior was unacceptable.

Immediately following the incident, I recognized the severity of my actions and took immediate steps to rectify the situation. I rushed my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being and to ensure that he received the necessary medical attention. I also took responsibility for the financial consequences of his hospital bills and offered to cover them entirely. I wanted to demonstrate my genuine concern and remorse for causing him harm.

In light of this unfortunate event, I would like to take this opportunity to extend my heartfelt apologies to the victim and his family. I cannot express enough my deep regret for the physical and emotional distress I have caused them. This incident has deeply impacted their lives, and I am truly sorry for the pain and inconvenience they have had to endure.

It is important to note, Your Honor, that I am 40 years old and have no criminal record. This incident does not reflect who I truly am as a person, nor is it indicative of my character. Throughout my life, I have strived to be a responsible and law-abiding citizen. I have always made it a priority to be a fair and considerate employer, dedicated to the well-being of my employees. However, on that fateful day, my anger got the best of me, and I acted in a way that is completely out of character for me.

Thank you for your understanding and attention.

Sincerely,
Aleksander Nowak

